CA Small Claims Court Forms
===========================

Fee Waiver Application Update
-----------------------------

Hello <%= @user.display_name %>,

There has been an update to your fee waiver application status.

<% case @status.to_s %>
<% when "approved" %>
*** APPROVED ***
<%= @status_message %>
<% when "denied" %>
*** NOT APPROVED ***
<%= @status_message %>
<% when "pending_review" %>
*** UNDER REVIEW ***
<%= @status_message %>
<% else %>
*** STATUS UPDATED ***
<%= @status_message %>
<% end %>

APPLICATION DETAILS
-------------------
Form: <%= @form_definition.code %> - <%= @form_definition.title %>
Status: <%= @status.to_s.titleize %>
Updated: <%= Time.current.strftime("%B %d, %Y at %I:%M %p") %>

<% if @status.to_s == "approved" %>
WHAT THIS MEANS
---------------
- Court filing fees will be waived for your case
- You may still need to pay for process server or other costs
- Keep a copy of your fee waiver approval for your records
- The waiver applies to the specific case mentioned
<% elsif @status.to_s == "denied" %>
YOUR OPTIONS
------------
- You may request a hearing to contest the decision
- You can reapply if your financial situation changes
- Contact the court clerk for information about payment plans
- Some courts offer reduced fees based on income
<% elsif @status.to_s == "pending_review" %>
WHAT HAPPENS NEXT
-----------------
- A court clerk will review your application
- You may be asked to provide additional documentation
- Review typically takes 1-5 business days
- You will receive an email when a decision is made
<% end %>

View your application at: <%= submission_url(@submission) %>

QUESTIONS?
----------
If you have questions about your fee waiver status, please contact your local Small Claims Court clerk's office directly.

